

#  PROJECT: Enterprise-Scale Production Infrastructure & Reliability Platform

(Applicable to VSCO, SAP Ariba, PhonePe)

This project models real production environments:

 VSCO ‚Üí B2C photo platform
 SAP Ariba ‚Üí B2B procurement SaaS
 PhonePe ‚Üí High-scale fintech & payments

---

#  1. ROLE: Linux System Administrator

### Key Responsibilities

 Provisioned and maintained Linux servers (RHEL/Rocky/Ubuntu) across production, staging, and dev environments.
 Managed file systems, LVM, NFS, SELinux, and OS hardening policies.
 Handled user management, permissions, ACL, sudo policies, and audit logging.
 Performed performance tuning (CPU, memory, I/O, kernel parameters).
 Automated repetitive tasks using Shell/Python.
 Troubleshot issues

 Managed patching cycles, kernel upgrades, and package management (YUM, DNF).

---

#  2. ROLE: Infrastructure Support Engineer

### Key Responsibilities

 Supported on-prem + cloud infrastructure (VMware, KVM, AWS/Azure).
 Monitored server health, resource utilization, and uptime issues.
 Implemented and maintained:

   Load balancers
   FirewallD
   DNS
   Reverse proxies (Nginx, HAProxy)
 Managed networking: VLANs, routing, DNS resolution issues, certificate renewals.
 Supported application deployments by ensuring servers, networking, and storage were ready.
 Troubleshot prod incidents, connectivity issues, and service failures.
 Ensured compliance with security policies, CIS standards, and audit requirements.

---

#  3. ROLE: DevOps Engineer

### Key Responsibilities

 Built CI/CD pipelines using Jenkins/GitHub Actions/GitLab CI.
 Automated:

   Build, test, scan
   Multi-arch image builds (`amd64`, `arm64`) using Podman
   Artifact push to JFrog
   Application deployment to Kubernetes
 Implemented Infrastructure as Code using Terraform.
 Built Golden Images using Packer + Ansible (RHEL-based).
 Managed configuration management using Ansible.
 Integrated security tools (Trivy, Aqua, Clair) into pipelines.
 Designed zero-downtime deployments using:

   Blue-Green
   Rolling
   Canary
 Automated logs/metrics pipelines.

---

#  4. ROLE: Site Reliability Engineer (SRE)

### Key Responsibilities

 Ensured 99.9%+ uptime for high-traffic services (VSCO media APIs, PhonePe UPI APIs, Ariba procurement modules).
 Built observability stack using:

   Prometheus
   Grafana
   Alertmanager
   Loki / ELK
 Defined SLOs, SLIs, error budgets, and reliability metrics.
 Handled 24√ó7 on-call, performing:

   Incident response
   Latency investigations
   Traffic/Throughput analysis
   RCA and postmortems
 Implemented service autoscaling, rate limiting, and reliability patterns.
 Troubleshot Kubernetes issues (CrashLoopBackOff, DNS breaks, pod evictions).
 Optimized performance for:

   API latency
   Database connections
   Thread pools
   JVM/Node/Python apps

---

#  PROJECT STRUCTURE 

#  PROJECT NAME: Hybrid Cloud Production Infrastructure & Reliability Platform

## 1. Problem Statement

Each company (VSCO, SAP Ariba, PhonePe) operates millions of users with:

 high traffic
 strict uptime requirements
 sensitive workloads
 complex distributed systems
  My role was to build and maintain a scalable, secure, automated infrastructure supporting these production services.

---

## 2. Architecture Components

### Compute

 On-prem VMs (VMware/KVM)
 Cloud VMs (AWS/Azure)
 Kubernetes clusters (EKS/AKS or on-prem K8s)

### Networking

 Load balancers
 DNS, DHCP
 VPC/Subnets/Security Groups
 Nginx reverse proxy
 API gateway

### Storage

 NFS / Ceph
 Cloud block storage
 S3 buckets / Object storage

### DevOps Tooling

 Terraform, Packer
 Jenkins/GitHub Actions
 Podman/Docker
 Ansible

### Observability

 Prometheus
 Grafana
 Alertmanager
 Loki / ELK
 Jaeger (tracing)

---

## 3. Key Deliverables

 Automated provisioning for 5000+ servers
 End-to-end CI/CD for microservices
 Kubernetes scaling + rollout automation
 Golden image pipeline for OS standardization
 Production observability dashboards
 SLO/SLA definitions for critical APIs
 Reduced mean time to recovery (MTTR)
 24√ó7 on-call rotation with RCA documentation

---

## 4. End Users (Domain-Specific)

### VSCO

 B2C photo editing users
 Content upload/download users
 Internal creative/editorial teams
 Product & engineering teams

### SAP Ariba

 B2B procurement teams
 Buyers & suppliers
 Vendor managers
 Enterprise integration teams
 InfoSec & compliance teams

### PhonePe

 B2C consumers making UPI payments
 B2B merchants using QR & settlement services
 B2A integrations (NPCI, govt billers)
 Risk, fraud, and compliance teams

